{"word":"ἐπαχθής","slug":"ἐπαχθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπαχθής</b></el> <el>(ἐπ-αχθής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄχθος'><el>ἄχθος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>heavy, ponderous</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>burdensome, annoying, grievous</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of persons, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}